If you're not modifying the internal state of the class, make the method `const`. Review the rest of the methods too. E.g.:

```
#!c++
public: void MoveAgent(Agent &_agent,
                       const ignition::math::Vector3<double> &_pos) const;
```

Consider using the `for range loop` syntax for this type of for loops:


```
#!c++

for (auto &team : this->teams)
  {
    for (auto &agent : team->members)
    {
      agent.status = Agent::Status::RELEASED;
    }
  }
```

Do not use inline comments if possible. Put the comments in this way:


```
#!c++

// highest priority
this->gameState->CheckTiming();  
// lowest priority
this->gameState->CheckDoubleTouch();
```
